article.headline: Charlotte 83, Gardner-Webb 51
article.story: CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) -- Leemire Goldwire scored 20 points as Charlotte overcame a sluggish start to beat Gardner-Webb 83-51 on Saturday. Lamont Mack added 11 points, while Charlie Coley and Charles Dewhurst both had double-doubles with 12 points and 11 rebounds each as the 49ers (7-4) snapped a two-game losing streak. Thomas Sanders scored 14 points and Nate Blank 11 for the Bulldogs (5-8), who could not keep pace with Charlotte on the way to their fourth straight defeat. Gardner-Webb shot less than 30 percent from the field, made only 2 of 18 three-point attempts, were outrebounded 50-36 and had 11 shots blocked. With Charlotte missing 10 of its first 13 shots, Gardner-Webb went up by six points twice in the first half. The last time was at 12-6 on Sanders layup with 13:58 left. But the 49ers quickly found their stride, with Goldwire nailing a 3-pointer with 5:56 remaining to cap a 21-7 run and put Charlotte up 27-19. The Bulldogs hit six straight free throws over the next minute to cut the 49ers lead to 27-25. But Goldwire hit consecutive 3-pointers to start a 14-4 run to close out the half. Charlotte led 43-29 at the break. The 49ers steadily increased their lead in the second half, with a Kyle Church 3-pointer putting Charlotte ahead 83-49 with 52.2 seconds remaining, its biggest margin of the game.
